#, no-wrap
msgid "Navigating folders\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:8
msgid ""
"![image](images/Folders-en.png) On the left side of the LightZone window is "
"the Folder Navigator that shows the folders on your computer. The Folder "
"Navigator looks and works much like a Finder Windows Explorer window in list "
"view mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:13
msgid ""
"The major difference, however, is that only folders and disks are shown -- "
"files are not. Instead, thumbnails for the photos in the selected folder are "
"displayed in the [thumbnails](Thumbnails.html) section of the window."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:17
msgid ""
"The Folder Navigator allows you to navigate to, select, and view the "
"thumbnails and [metadata](Metadata.html) for photos in folders on your "
"computer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "To navigate to a folder:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:23
msgid "Click the triangles plus signs '+' to expand the folders."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:23
msgid "Select the desired folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:26
msgid ""
"![image](images/Tools-Navigator-en.png) Additionally, the navigator tool "
"buttons can be used to navigate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:29
msgid ""
"The **Back/Forward** buttons can be used to navigate either back or forward "
"to the folder you were previously in."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Navigating_Folders.markdown.txt:31
msgid "The **Path** button can be used to navigate up the folder tree quickly."
msgstr ""

